Production, imports, exports. and consumption of timber products, by major product, 1950-87

Dataset containing statistics for various timber products (hardwood and softwood). All units are Million cubic ft (roundwood equivalent) unless otherwise specified.

ulrich4

Format

A data frame with 38 observations of 24 variables

Source

Based on data published by the U.S. Departments of Commerce and Agriculture. Data for 1900-49 in "The demand and price situation for forest products 1964", table 2 (31),

Details

  • AllProducts.Prod Production for all timber products
  • AllProducts.Consump Consumption for all timber products
  • Tot.Prod Total Production for major timber products
  • Tot.Imports Total Imports for major timber products
  • Tot.Exports Total Exports for major timber products
  • Tot.Consump Total Consumption for major timber products
  • Lumber.Prod Lumber Products Prodcution
  • Lumber.Imports Lumber Products Imports
  • Lumber.Exports Lumber Products Exports
  • Lumber.Consump Lumber Products Consumption
  • PlywoodVeneer.Prod Plywood and Veneer Products Production
  • PlywoodVeneer.Imports Plywood and Veneer Products Imports
  • PlywoodVeneer.Exports Plywood and Veneer Products Exports
  • PlywoodVeneer.Consump Plywood and Veneer Products Consumption
  • PulpProducts.Prod Pulp Products Production
  • PulpProducts.Imports Pulp Products Imports
  • PulpProducts.Exports Pulp Products Exports
  • PulpProducts.Consump Pulp Products Consumption
  • OtherIndProducts.ProdandConsump Production and Consumption for other industrial products
  • Logs.Imports Log Imports
  • Logs.Exports Log Exports
  • PulpwoodChip.Exports Pulpwood-chip Exports
  • Fuelwood.ProdandConsump Production and Consumption for fuelwood products
  • LogChipExports.PercofProduction Log and Chip exports as a percent of production
